&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Gyffin Receptionist&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;A vacancy has arisen within Gyffin Surgery in Conwy for a part time receptionist working 22 hours per week over 4 afternoons (days to be confirmed), working with an enthusiastic team just outside Conwy Castle, this renovated Chapel is situated on the Woodlands in Conwy. The Practice is a Health Board run Practice with approximately 4,000 patients with a full compliment of receptionists / administrators and nursing team. We currently have regular locum GPs working in Gyffin but have now received interest for salaried GP positions. This has a warm and friendly atmosphere where you will be made to feel at home.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is essential for this post. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing Date: 10/11/2020 &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact: &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Debbie Searle&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title: Practice Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: debbie.searle@wales.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number: 01492 596381 &lt;/p&gt;
